1. e4 c5 {Already a kind of a surprise. Obviously, Ivanchuk has vast
experience in the Sicilian, however, in his tournament situation when a draw
would secure him clear first, some solid opening was expected. But, you can
never know, what to expect from Ivanchuk!} 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e6 5.
Nc3 Qc7 6. Be3 a6 7. Qd2 Nf6 8. O-O-O Bb4 {So, it is one of the sharpest
variations in the Paulsen.} 9. f3 Ne5 10. Nb3 b5 (10... Bxc3 $6 11. bxc3 {is
in White's favour since the dark squares in Black's camp are vulnerable.}) 11.
Bd4 {This move is more tempting, though the prophylactic 11.Kb1 is also a
common move here.} (11. Kb1 Nc4 (11... Be7 12. Qf2 d6 13. Bb6 Qb8 14. Bd4 O-O
15. g4 Nfd7 16. Rg1 b4 17. Na4 a5 18. f4 Nc6 19. Be3 Ba6 20. g5 Rc8 $132 {0-1
Macieja,B (2599)-Iotov,V (2531)/Plovdiv BUL 2008/The Week in Chess 703 (69)})
12. Bxc4 bxc4 13. Nc1 Rb8 14. Bf4 (14. Ka1 $6 O-O 15. Bf4 e5 16. Bg5 Ne8 17.
N1e2 d6 18. a3 a5 19. Qc1 Be6 20. Na2 f5 21. Nec3 Qb7 22. Rhf1 Bc5 23. Rfe1 f4
$17 {0-1 Morozevich,A (2755)-Vitiugov,N (2594)/Moscow RUS 2007/The Week in
Chess 685 (71)}) 14... e5 15. Bg5 Qb6 16. N1e2 O-O 17. Bxf6 Ba3 18. b3 Qxf6 19.
Nd5 Qd8 20. f4 $1 $14 {1-0 Cheparinov,I (2670)-Pelletier,Y (2609)/Crete 2007/
CBM 121 (30)}) 11... Be7 (11... Bb7 12. Kb1 Be7 13. Qf2 (13. Na5 d6 14. Ne2 {
1/2-1/2 Ivanchuk,V (2740)-Ljubojevic,L (2600)/Belgrade 1995/CBM 051}) 13... Rc8
14. a3 O-O 15. g4 d6 16. g5 Nfd7 17. Rg1 Nc6 18. Be3 b4 19. axb4 Nxb4 20. f4
Rfe8 21. f5 exf5 22. exf5 Bf8 23. Rd4 $16 {1-0 Cheparinov,I (2550)-Pogorelov,R
(2451)/Dos Hermanas 2004/CBM 099 ext (41)}) 12. Qf2 {Cheparinov deviates from
his own game, obviously suspecting some improvement which might have been
prepared by Vassily Ivanchuk.} (12. Kb1 d6 13. Qf2 O-O 14. g4 Nfd7 15. Rg1 b4
16. Na4 Qc6 17. Nb6 Nxb6 18. Na5 Qd7 19. Bxb6 Rb8 20. f4 Ng6 21. Nc4 Qc6 22.
Ba7 Rb5 23. f5 Ne5 24. Nxe5 Rxe5 25. Bd4 $16 {1-0 Cheparinov,I (2625)
-Middelburg,T (2413)/Netherlands 2006/EXT 2007 (38)}) 12... d6 13. g4 O-O {Now
the position is similar to one that arises in the other Sicilian variation: 1.
e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.Be3 e6 7.f3 b5 8.Qd2 and so on.
Castling on opposite sides always promises a sharp, double-edged fight.} 14. g5
Nfd7 15. Rg1 Bb7 16. Kb1 Rfc8 17. Rg3 $2 $146 {Just a bad novelty. Needless to
say, that in such a sharp position one mistake is enough to lose the game.} (
17. a3 {This move is necessary to prevent b5-b4.} Nc4 18. Bxc4 Qxc4 {I think
that the recapture by the queen is preferable. This way Black keeps his
queenside pawns mobile, compared to the position which arises after 18...bxc4.}
(18... bxc4 19. Nc1 Rab8 20. N1e2 Bc6 21. Ka1 Qa5 22. Na2 e5 23. Bc3 Qc7 24.
Ng3 g6 25. Nf1 Nc5 26. Ne3 $14 {1-0 Kasparov,G (2838)-Ye Jiangchuan (2667)/
Bled 2002/EXT 2003 (66)}) 19. Rg4 Qc7 (19... a5 $5 $13 {Ribli[%cal Gb5b4]}) 20.
f4 e5 21. Be3 exf4 22. Bxf4 Ne5 23. Rg3 Bf8 24. h4 $14 {1-0 Lahno,K (2472)
-Goloshchapov,A (2577)/Kharkov 2004/CBM 103 (41)[%csl Yd5][%cal Gh4h5,Gc3d5]})
17... b4 18. Na4 {The knight has to go to this unfortunate square.} Bd8 $1 {
Covering b6 square and preparing 19...Bc6. The Na4 has no place to retreat to.}
19. Nc1 {What else?} Bc6 20. b3 Bxa4 21. bxa4 Nc6 22. Be3 Qb8 $1 {Preparing
either 23...Nb6 or 23...Bb6.} ({An immediate} 22... Nb6 $2 {would
unnecessarily give up a pawn:} 23. Bxb6 Qxb6 24. Qxb6 Bxb6 25. Rxd6) 23. Rh3 {
An attempt to create mating threats along the h-file is too primitive but,
White has no other idea instead. His position on the queenside is permanently
corrupted.} Nb6 24. Qh4 (24. Bxb6 Qxb6 25. Qxb6 Bxb6 26. Rxd6 Be3 $17 {White
has too many weaknesses.}) 24... h6 {The only defence but, sufficient.} 25. Qg3
(25. Qh5 Nxa4 26. gxh6 Nc3+ 27. Ka1 Nxd1 28. hxg7 Bf6+ $19) 25... Nxa4 26. Rxd6
hxg5 27. Bd3 Bf6 {White has no threats, meanwhile his king is doomed.} 28. e5
Bxe5 29. Rh8+ {Trying to shatter Chukky's confidence but, not in this
tournament!} Kxh8 30. Qh3+ Kg8 31. Qh7+ Kf8 32. Rd7 Nc3+ 33. Ka1 Nb5+ {With
this win Ivanchuk set the seal on a convincing overall victory with a superb
result: 8 points out of 10!} 0-1

